<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.176180>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Metavermilia ogasawaraensis n. sp. A, holotype crown and trunk. B, operculum of paratype NHM- 2006.2039. C, anterior part of tube of holotype. Scales are 1 mm (A, C), 0.5 mm (B)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/176180/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.176181>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Operculum of Metavermilia species. A— multicristata. B, C— taenia. D, E— annobonensis. F— nates. G— arctica. H, I— acanthophora. J— yamazatoi. K— gravitesta. L— spicata. M— truncata. N, O— inflata. P, Qovata. R, S— ogasawaraensis n. sp. T, U, V— nanshaensis. Figures are drawn from the figures of paper, traced using black ink on the transparent sheet. A to F after Zibrowius (1971), G from Kupriyanova (1993), H to Q after Imajima (1996), R and S are original, T—V after Sun (1998)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/176181/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

